Use `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in `MauiProgram.cs` to hook platform-native callbacks:

```csharp
builder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>
{
#if ANDROID
    events.AddAndroid(android => android
        .OnPause(activity =>
        {
            // Runs when activity loses focus
        })
        .OnStop(activity =>
        {
            // Runs when activity is no longer visible
        }));
#elif IOS || MACCATALYST
    events.AddiOS(ios => ios
        .DidEnterBackground(app =>
        {
            // Runs when app enters background
        }));
#endif
});
```

**Key points:**

- Android `OnPause` maps to the cross-platform `Deactivated` event (lost focus, may still be visible). `OnStop` maps to `Stopped` (fully backgrounded).
- iOS `DidEnterBackground` maps to the cross-platform `Stopped` event.
- If you don't need platform-specific details, you can use the cross-platform `Window.Stopped` event instead — it fires on both platforms when the app backgrounds.
- Keep handlers fast (<2s) to avoid ANR on Android or watchdog kills on iOS.
